                            <comment id="17195529" author="emilles" created="Mon, 14 Sep 2020 15:29:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;While compiling &lt;tt&gt;BTCTestSupport&lt;/tt&gt; there is a &lt;tt&gt;CastExpression&lt;/tt&gt; with null type.  Can you run your build with debug breakpoint set in &lt;tt&gt;CastExpression&lt;/tt&gt; constructor looking for null &lt;tt&gt;type&lt;/tt&gt; param?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17195789" author="msgilligan" created="Tue, 15 Sep 2020 00:31:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I set a breakpoint in the CastExpression constructor with a condition of `type == null` and it was not trigged. (As I check I also tried `type != null` and it was triggered many times)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t know if I trust IntelliJ debugging GroovyC being run through Gradle, but that&apos;s what I am seeing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17196208" author="emilles" created="Tue, 15 Sep 2020 14:57:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To debug the Groovy compiler, I needed to add &lt;tt&gt;groovyOptions.fork = false&lt;/tt&gt; to &lt;tt&gt;tasks.withType(GroovyCompile)&lt;/tt&gt; in build.gradle in addition to &lt;tt&gt;-Dorg.gradle.debug=true&lt;/tt&gt; on the gradle command line.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The null cast is created by &lt;tt&gt;TraitReceiverTransformer&lt;/tt&gt; when it is processing a field reference for the &quot;client&quot; variable in &lt;tt&gt;BTCTestSupport&lt;/tt&gt;.  If I change &quot;client&quot; to &quot;getClient()&quot;, the problem moves to the next property reference (fundingSource).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will try to isolate the problem in a smaller set of sources.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17196403" author="emilles" created="Tue, 15 Sep 2020 17:17:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/groovy/pull/1369&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/groovy/pull/1369&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17196414" author="msgilligan" created="Tue, 15 Sep 2020 17:29:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt;&#160; I will try to isolate the problem in a smaller set of sources.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yeah, I really went hog-wild with Traits and inheritance (trying to get as much functionality into some Spock integration tests as possible)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt;&#160; &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/groovy/pull/1369&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/groovy/pull/1369&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The PR means you were able to recreate and fix?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17196422" author="emilles" created="Tue, 15 Sep 2020 17:33:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, fully repeatable with the test case that was included in the PR.  And yes, it&apos;s fixed from what I can tell.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17196429" author="msgilligan" created="Tue, 15 Sep 2020 17:40:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Awesome. Thanks! I guess I&apos;ll stick with 3.0.4 until 3.0.6 comes out...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17196828" author="paulk" created="Wed, 16 Sep 2020 09:46:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Proposed PR merged, thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17204277" author="msgilligan" created="Tue, 29 Sep 2020 20:30:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve verified that Groovy 3.0.6 fixes the ConsensusJ build. Thanks again!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
